File: Peter Moyo is seeking damages of R250 million. JOHANNESBURG - Old Mutual has received a summons from Peter Moyo seeking damages of R250-million. The insurer has confirmed receipt of the summons from the 'axed'-CEO and says it will defend any claim vigorously. Old Mutual says this amount is in addition to the R35.5-million salary he received and the R4-million payout for six-months' notice. Moyo was again refused entry to his office last month. READ: Old Mutual given 10 days to explain their actions The High Court ordered his temporary reinstatement after he was fired for an alleged conflict of interest. Moyo said Old Mutual can't continue hiding behind their lawyers. READ: Peter Moyo back in court against Old Mutual Moyo was fired in June over an alleged conflict of interest.